.\" Manpage for menmath.
.TH man 1 "10 December 2025" "1" "menmath man page"

.SH NAME
menmath \- utility to train mental math

.SH SYNOPSIS
menmath [--warm <n> <l1> <h1> <l2> <h2>] [--sum <n> <l1> <h1> <l2> <h2>] [--mult <n> <l1> <h1> <l2> <h2>] [--diff <n> <l1> <h1>] [--change <n> <note>]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Run menmath, and it offer simple random arithmetic exercise. Solve it (in mind), type answer in terminal, and press enter.

.SH EXAMPLES

menmath --sum 10 11 101 11 101

Train summation in 10 exercises the first number in range from 11 to 101, and the second number in range from 11 to 101.

menmath --warm 5 5 8 5 8 --sum 10 11 101 11 101 --mult 10 11 101 0 11 --diff 10 0 101 --change 10 2000

Warm up in 5 exercises first digit in range from 5 to 8, and second digit from 5 to 8. Train summation in 10 exercises the first number in range from 11 to 101, and the second number in range from 11 to 101. Multiplication in 10 exersises the first number from 11 to 101, the second number is from 0 to 1. Subtraction in 10 exersises where numbers from 0 to 101, but the second number always lower than first. Finally train change counting in 10 exersises for the banknote in 2000 (dollars, pounds watewer).

menmath

The same as above.

.SH OPTIONS

--warm - the same as --sum, but suppose to exercise in range 0 - 10.

--sum - summation.

--mul - multiplication.

--diff - difference.

--change - change counter trainer.

.SH
INSTALLATION

git clone https://github.com/AlexeyReshetnyak/menmath
cd menmath
make all
make install

.SH AUTHOR
Alexey Reshetnyak (https://github.com/AlexeyReshetnyak/menmath)
